%% [IMPLEMENTED] Organization identity is separated from global user roles.
%% [IMPLEMENTED] Tenant selection uses X-Organization-Id or preview query parameters, then loads an active organization_members row.
%% [IMPLEMENTED] Workspace identity is organizations.slug and a computed /workspace/{slug} URL. There is no workspace_urls table.
%% [IMPLEMENTED] Most CMS records store organization_id directly after migration 0008; some child rows also derive it from parent rows through triggers.
%% [PARTIAL] organization_status and organization_member_status include suspended/deleted/invited values, but current organization routes mostly create, update, delete, revoke, accept, leave, and transfer ownership.
%% [PARTIAL] organization_invitations stores token_hash and accepted_at, but not accepted_user_id. The accepting user is matched at runtime by lower(users.email) = lower(invitation.email).
%% [PARTIAL] organization_domains stores verification_token, status, and verified_at, but no verification endpoint was found.
%% [PARTIAL] Last-owner protection is enforced in organization route code, not as a SQL constraint.
